name: simplejson
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "3.18.1" %}

package:
  name: simplejson
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/s/simplejson/simplejson-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 746086e3ef6d74b53599df31b491d88a355abf2e31c837137dd90f8c4561cafa

build:
  number: 0
  skip: true  # [py<36]
  script:
    - export REQUIRE_SPEEDUPS=1  # [not win]
    - set REQUIRE_SPEEDUPS=1  # [win]
    - {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - simplejson
    - simplejson._speedups   # [python_impl != 'pypy']
    - simplejson.tests
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: http://github.com/simplejson/simplejson
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Simple, fast, extensible JSON encoder/decoder for Python

  description: |
    simplejson is a simple, fast, complete, correct and extensible
    JSON <http://json.org> encoder and decoder for Python 2.5+ and
    Python 3.3+. It is pure Python code with no dependencies, but includes
    an optional C extension for a serious speed boost.
  doc_url: http://simplejson.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/simplejson/simplejson

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ainafp
    - ocefpaf
